-- O’Neill Says ‘Categorically No’ That Pandit Departed Over Pay
-- B y   D o n a l   G r i f f i n
-- 2012-10-16T21:00:50Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-16/o-neill-says-categorically-no-that-pandit-departed-over-pay.html
Michael O’Neill , the chairman of
Citigroup Inc., said the departure of Chief Executive Officer
Vikram Pandit wasn’t tied to compensation.  “Let me start with pay, the answer to that is
categorically no,” O’Neill said today on a conference call held
by the New York-based bank when asked about the reason for
Pandit’s departure.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Donal Griffin in New York at 
